  "texts": [
    "The test images were acquired with aberrations sampled uniformly within ±20 µm (wd) and ±5 (stigmators).",
    "All models were developed and trained using PyTorch 28 1.9.0 and the open source framework elektronn3 (https://github.com/ELEKTRONN/ elektronn3) with mini-batches, L 1 loss (mean absolute error), step learning rate scheduler (a factor of 0.99 every 2000 steps) and the AdamW optimizer 29.",
    "The image-to-scalar architecture used seven convolutional layers (valid convolution; 3D kernels to share weights across the two inputs using a z-kernel size of 1) followed by three fully connected layers (Table 2).",
    "The convolutional layers were constructed as follows: convolution, batch normalization, activation (ReLU), max-pooling, and dropout (rate p = 0.1).",
    "For different input shapes, the parameters of the fully connected layer (rows 8-10 in Table 2) were adjusted as follows:"
